======================================================================
PART 2: SPECTRAL GAP vs H
  'Spectral gap' = largest real eigenvalue of A
  Expected: H-maximizers have largest spectral gap
======================================================================

--- n = 5 ---
  Correlation(H, spectral_radius) = 0.860853
  Correlation(H, max_real_eigenvalue) = 0.860853
  H-maximizer (H=15): spectral_radius in [np.float64(1.8637065278191873), np.float64(1.8637065278191882), np.float64(1.8637065278191884)]
  H-minimizer (H=1): spectral_radius in [np.float64(0.0)]

--- n = 6 ---
  Correlation(H, spectral_radius) = 0.818894
  Correlation(H, max_real_eigenvalue) = 0.818894
  H-maximizer (H=45): spectral_radius in [np.float64(2.4142135623730896), np.float64(2.4142135623730905), np.float64(2.4142135623730914)]
  H-minimizer (H=1): spectral_radius in [np.float64(0.0)]

