======================================================================
PART 5: EIGENVALUE STATISTICS (Random Matrix Theory)
  Tournament A is a random {0,1} matrix with A+A^T = J-I
  What is the eigenvalue distribution?
======================================================================
  n=8, 1000 samples
  Eigenvalue real parts: mean=0.0000, std=1.1481, range=[-0.5000, 3.4464]
  Eigenvalue imag parts: mean=0.0000, std=1.1481, range=[-2.4204, 2.4204]

  Expected: mean real = (n-1)/2 = 3.5 (row sum average)
  Note: A has row sums = out-degrees, trace = 0
  So sum(eigenvalues) = trace(A) = 0, but eigenvalues not centered at 0

  Correlation(H, spectral_radius) at n=8: 0.0336
  Correlation(H, max_real_eig) at n=8: 0.0336
  Mean H = 311.93, n!/2^(n-1) = 315.00

